Nigerian singer Dbanj has spoken out after his 13-month-old son, Little Daniel Oyebanjo lll, drowned in a freak accident at their palatial home in Ikoyi, Lagos, while Dbanj was in LA for the 2018 BET Awards. He wrote on social media: "We want to use this medium to thank everyone that has extended a hand of support to us during this period. On behalf of myself and my family, we are awed by the demonstration of love and care from both near and afar. May god bless you all. From the Oyebanjos." His fans condoled with him. Samuelteex: Big brother stay strong, God is your strength.... funkesotunde: For this pain you shall have multiple GAIN. ademolaafeezco: We love bro ....stay strong... this accident is just a test trial...